
  <sn><md>### CAM Pathway

(Crassulacean Acid Metabolism)

CAM pathway is a photosynthetic adaptation found in `plants of arid and desert environments` (e.g., cactus, pineapple, agave).
These plants `open stomata at night` to conserve water and store CO₂ as organic acids.
During **daytime**, stored CO₂ is released internally for photosynthesis.

+++ ascii diagram

```text
                    CAM PATHWAY (CRASSULACEAN ACID METABOLISM)

============================== NIGHT (STOMATA OPEN) ==============================

                   ATM CO₂ (Atmospheric Carbon Dioxide)
                               |
                               v
                     CO₂ + PEP (Phosphoenolpyruvate)
                               |
                               v
                       [PEPC / PEPCase]
                  (PEP Carboxylase Enzyme)
                               |
                               v
                OAA (Oxaloacetic Acid, 4C compound)
                               |
                               v
                     Converted to Malate (4C)
                               |
                               v
                Stored as Malic Acid in Vacuole (Night Storage)


============================== DAY (STOMATA CLOSED) ==============================

                 Vacuole Releases Malic Acid (Malate)
                               |
                               v
                        Decarboxylation
                               |
                               v
               CO₂ Released Internally for Calvin Cycle (C₃)
                               |
                               v
                     Sugar Synthesis (Photosynthesis)
                               |
                               v
                     Pyruvate → Regenerates PEP
                               |
                               v
                           CYCLE CONTINUES


---------------------------
LEGENDS
---------------------------
ATM CO₂ = Atmospheric Carbon Dioxide  
PEP = Phosphoenolpyruvate  
PEPC / PEPCase = PEP Carboxylase  
OAA = Oxaloacetic Acid (4C)  
Malate = 4-carbon organic acid  
Calvin Cycle (C₃) = CO₂ fixation pathway  
Vacuole = Storage organelle  
```

