<sn><md>### Significance

1. Stomata open at night, saving large amounts of water.
2. Very high water-use efficiency, ideal for drought.
3. Low photorespiration due to internal CO₂ release.
4. Helps plants survive in hot, dry, desert climates.
5. Time-separated CO₂ fixation increases photosynthesis efficiency.
